# Secrets Safety

## Never commit
- `.env` files (gitignored at repo root)
- `secrets/*.json` service-account keys
- `vertexai_sa.json` or any credential JSON

## CI authentication
- Use **Workload Identity Federation (WIF)** in GitHub Actions — no JSON keys in CI (`WIF_PROVIDER`, `WIF_SERVICE_ACCOUNT`).

## Local development
- Copy from `.env.example` on first setup; leave `GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS` empty if no SA JSON is mounted.
- Backend starts gracefully without Firestore credentials; Firestore-dependent endpoints return auth errors.

## Agent behaviour
- Never print, log, or embed secret values in commits, PRs, or generated docs.
- When adding new env vars, document them in `.env.example` — not with real values.
